{
  "texts": [
    "Data pre-processing.",
    "Raw Raman spectra were backgroundsubtracted with the arPLS algorithm 71, then cosmic spikes were removed by detecting them based on derivative value and removing them via interpolation.",
    "Finally, spectra were normalized by subtracting the mean and dividing by the standard deviation.",
    "Since multiple spectra are available for a single sample, splitting them into training and validation sets is unnecessary.",
    "Instead, the splitting should be done on a sample level, with all the spectra of a sample put in the same split."
  ]
}